{"article_id":"wEzGUCMkPN5LD3DD","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Democratic-controlled US House of Representatives has voted to end a partial government shutdown ,","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"but the move looks certain to be vetoed by President Donald Trump .","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"Mr Trump has said","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"he will reject any measure","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"that does not provide funding for his proposed US-Mexico border wall .","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"New House Speaker Nancy Pelosi ,","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"who will resume negotiations with Mr Trump on Friday ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"branded the wall immoral .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"The new Congress is considered the most diverse in history .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"The bills","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"passed by the House of Representatives","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"would fund homeland security operations ,","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"including $ 1.3bn in border security ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"until 8 February ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"and fund several other agencies until September .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"However , it requires Senate approval , and sign off from the president ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"in order to become law .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Republicans currently have a majority in the Senate ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"and majority leader Mitch McConnell has said","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Republicans there would not back measures","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that Mr Trump did not support .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Mr McConnell called the Democrats ' move a `` total nonstarter '' and a `` political sideshow '' .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"However , Democrats argue","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"that the bills are nearly identical to ones","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"passed by the Senate last month ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"before Mr Trump insisted","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"wall funding must be included .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Nancy Pelosi , a Democrat from California , was elected as Speaker of the House for a second time","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"- becoming the third most powerful politician in the US .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"She previously led the House from 2007-11 -","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"and remains the only female","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"to hold the position .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"She invited the children and grandchildren of House Representatives","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"to join her","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"as she was sworn in ,","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"saying :","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"`` I 'm particularly proud to be a woman Speaker of the House of this Congress ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"which marks the 100th year of women","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"having the right","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"to vote . ''","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"Later , she told reporters :","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"`` We 're not doing a wall ...","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"a wall is an immorality between countries .","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"It 's an old way","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"of thinking .","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"It is n't cost effective . ''","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"She added","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"that spending money on `` more infrastructure at the ports of entry '' and better technology would be more efficient .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"As of Thursday , 102 women serve in the 435-seat House , an all-time high ,","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"including 36 newly elected members and a record 43 women of colour .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"While Republican women marked some firsts this past election season ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"like Marsha Blackburn becoming the first female Tennessee senator ,","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"the vast majority of these new lawmakers are Democrats .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"The first Muslim congresswomen - Michigan 's Rashida Tlaib ,","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"who took her oath on the Koran ,","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"and Minnesota 's Ilhan Omar ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"who became the first person","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"to wear a hijab in Congress","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"The first Native American congresswomen","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"- New Mexico 's Debra Haaland and Kansas ' Sharice Davids New York 's Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez , 29 , the youngest woman","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"to be elected to Congress","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"Carol Miller of West Virginia is the only new female Republican representative ,","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"bringing the total number of conservative women in the House to 13","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"- a decrease from 23 before the mid-term elections .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"The partial US government shutdown began","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"when Congress and Mr Trump failed to reach an agreement over a budget bill in December .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"The Republicans had passed an initial funding bill","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"including $ 5bn","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"( £4bn )","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"for the wall ,","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"when they still had a majority in the House ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"but they could not get the necessary 60 votes in the 100-seat Senate .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Democrats won the majority of the House in the November mid-term elections ,","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"and the new representatives were sworn in on Thursday .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"`` We 're asking the president to open up government , ''","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Ms Pelosi told the Today show before the first session of the new House .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"`` We have given the Republicans a chance","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"to take yes for an answer . ''","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"The president is due to resume budget talks with top Democrats and Republicans on Friday morning .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"The White House says","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"it is again floating the idea of a deal for 'Dreamers '","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"- immigrants","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"who illegally entered the US as children .","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"Democrats want to ensure","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"that these individuals are shielded from deportation ,","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"but have insisted","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"that they will not support a deal over wall funding .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"Vice-President Mike Pence told Fox News","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"the deal was being `` talked about '' ,","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"but that Mr Trump said","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"no deal was possible `` without a wall '' .","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"Meanwhile , some vulnerable Republican senators up for re-election in 2020 have spoken out in favour","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"of approving the budget bills","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"to end the government shutdown .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Senator Cory Gardner of Colorado was the first to do so ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"telling The Hill on Thursday","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"that Congress should reopen the government","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"and let wall negotiations continue afterwards .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"Maine Senator Susan Collins echoed this view ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"suggesting","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"the president should sign the agreed upon spending bills first","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"so federal employees could get back to work ,","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"Politico reported .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"Mr Trump pushed back on Friday against Democrats","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"who are calling for him to be removed from office .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"The Republican president tweeted","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"that his political enemies only want to impeach him","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"because he is `` the most successful '' .","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"Skip Twitter post by @ realDonaldTrump","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"How do you impeach a president","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"who has won perhaps the greatest election of all time ,","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"done nothing wrong","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"( no Collusion with Russia ,","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"it was the Dems that Colluded ) ,","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"had the most successful first two years of any president ,","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"and is the most popular Republican in party history 93 % ?","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"January 4 , 2019","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"Report","depth":3},{"id":120,"text":"After being sworn in on Thursday ,","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"Ms Tlaib used an expletive","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"to describe the president","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"while vowing to impeach him .","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"But fellow Democratic representative and civil rights icon John Lewis criticised her `` inappropriate '' remark ,","depth":6},{"id":125,"text":"telling reporters","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"impeachment talk `` is a little premature '' .","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"Ms Pelosi said","depth":5},{"id":128,"text":"they must `` wait and see '' what happens with special counsel Robert Mueller 's inquiry into Russia 's alleged meddling in the 2016 US election .","depth":5},{"id":129,"text":"About 25 % of the US federal government has no funding","depth":5},{"id":130,"text":"Nine departments have been affected ,","depth":6},{"id":131,"text":"including Homeland Security , Justice , Housing , Agriculture , Commerce , Interior , and the Treasury","depth":6},{"id":132,"text":"Around 800,000 federal workers are now furloughed","depth":6},{"id":133,"text":"- that is , temporarily laid off due to a lack of funding -","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"or working without pay","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"Native American tribes","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"who receive substantial federal funding","depth":5},{"id":137,"text":"are struggling","depth":4},{"id":138,"text":"More women than ever before won seats in Congress in the 2018 mid-terms .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":277,"left":267,"right":276,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":267,"left":257,"right":266,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":165,"right":256,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":155,"right":164,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":147,"right":154,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":146,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":140,"right":145,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":142,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":2,"right":141,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":141,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":143,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":143,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":152,"right":153,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":151,"right":14,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":151,"left":148,"right":150,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":148,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":149,"right":13,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":159,"right":163,"relation":"advers